HEADWORD: Immeability
<hw>Im`me*a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + L. <ets>meabilis</ets> passable, fr.
<ets>meare</ets> to pass.]</ety> <def>Lack of power to pass, or to
permit passage; impassableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Immeability</qex> of the juices.</q>
